Two police officers were found dead with bullet wounds to their heads in Thaba Nchu on Friday.The two officers who lived together are suspected to have got into a fight before the male partner shot and killed his partner and later turned the gun on himself.Spokesman for police minister Fikile Mbalula, Vuyo Mhaga said a police captain from Selisesha police found the bodies of the cops while responding to the shooting incident. They had gunshot wounds to the head. He said they had been living together and had children. &#8220;It is suspected that the male officer shot and killed his partner and turned the gun on himself,&#8221; he said. Police Minister Fikile Mbalula has sent his condolences to the family. &#8220;I would like to send my sincere condolences to the family and loved ones of the deceased. Losing someone you love is a very painful experience,&#8221; Mbalula said. Police are investigating the circumstances leading to the two&#8217;s deaths.